<!--            DESIGN CONSIDERATIONS                              -->
<!--
    This is from HTML 4.0 Strict DTD, which excludes the presentation
    attributes and elements that W3C expects to phase out as
    support for style sheets matures.

    The element type names retain the same case as in the original
    HTML 4.0 DTD, and, therefore, do not conform to SoftQuad style.

    In creating an XML-compatible module, many comments were moved
    out of element and attribute declarations, and single
    declarations declaring multiple element types (i.e. "<!ELEMENT
    (a|b|c) ... >") were broken into multiple declarations, one for
    each element.

          Draft: -Date: 1998/03/27 11:54:38-

